A 14-year-old girl was reported missing by her mother in May 2018, later found cohabiting with a 25-year-old man, with whom she subsequently had a child.


The Special POCSO Court convicted the accused under Sections 6 of the POCSO Act, 376(2)(n) and 376(3) IPC (rape of a minor), and 363, 366 IPC (kidnapping and abduction), sentencing him to 20 years’ rigorous imprisonment.


The Calcutta High Court (October 2023) set aside the conviction for rape and POCSO offences under Article 226 read with Section 482 Cr.P.C, holding the relationship to be “romantic” and “non-exploitative.” The Court also made general observations on teenage relationships, advising adolescent girls to “control their urges.”


